1
00:00:45,296 --> 00:00:47,773
Hello? Cielo, babe.

2
00:00:47,799 --> 00:00:52,386
María, hi.
What?

3
00:00:52,511 --> 00:00:55,447
She was born?

4
00:00:55,473 --> 00:00:57,616
And how is she?

5
00:00:57,642 --> 00:01:01,813
Is she all right?
Is everything okay?

6
00:01:01,938 --> 00:01:04,916
Thank God!

7
00:01:04,941 --> 00:01:07,877
No, no.

8
00:01:07,902 --> 00:01:09,378
I'm stuck here on the 30.

9
00:01:09,403 --> 00:01:11,823
I think there was
an accident. I don't know.

10
00:01:11,948 --> 00:01:15,242
No, no, no,
don't wake her up.

11
00:01:15,367 --> 00:01:17,929
Tell her I'm on my way.

12
00:01:17,954 --> 00:01:20,472
I'll be there any second now.

13
00:01:20,498 --> 00:01:23,334
Fine, thanks.
See you.

14
00:02:01,873 --> 00:02:04,892
Cielo, babe.

15
00:02:07,879 --> 00:02:09,981
Meet your daughter.

16
00:02:10,006 --> 00:02:12,024
Hi.

17
00:02:23,644 --> 00:02:26,705
Congratulations, Walter.

18
00:02:26,731 --> 00:02:29,441
Ernesto, I'm sorry.
I didn't see you.

19
00:02:29,567 --> 00:02:31,836
Don't worry.

20
00:02:31,861 --> 00:02:35,447
Ernesto brought
me here.

21
00:02:35,573 --> 00:02:37,909
Valentina wanted to come
out so hard

22
00:02:38,034 --> 00:02:39,577
that we thought she was going
to come in the car.

23
00:02:39,702 --> 00:02:41,220
Yes.

24
00:02:41,245 --> 00:02:43,973
Almost like in the news.

25
00:02:43,998 --> 00:02:46,558
I'm glad it didn't come to that.

26
00:02:46,584 --> 00:02:47,977
Thank you, Ernesto.

27
00:02:48,002 --> 00:02:50,395
No, it's my pleasure.

28
00:02:50,421 --> 00:02:52,272
I'm going to leave

29
00:02:52,297 --> 00:02:55,567
so you three are alone.

30
00:02:55,593 --> 00:02:58,721
Thank you.
I can't thank you enough.

31
00:02:58,846 --> 00:03:01,240
No, it's my pleasure.

32
00:03:01,265 --> 00:03:02,950
It's what I had to do.

33
00:03:02,975 --> 00:03:05,477
- Thank you.
- Congratulations.

34
00:03:05,603 --> 00:03:06,996
Bye, Walter.

35
00:03:07,021 --> 00:03:10,041
See you.

36
00:03:17,322 --> 00:03:18,908
Are you okay?
Is everything okay?

37
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:22,011
Yes, I'm perfect.

38
00:03:24,288 --> 00:03:27,125
I just wish
you'd been here.

39
00:03:31,253 --> 00:03:32,688
And the rest?

40
00:03:32,713 --> 00:03:35,049
Henry and María
took Junior

41
00:03:35,174 --> 00:03:37,093
to eat
something.

42
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:39,011
He has been
such a trooper.

43
00:03:39,137 --> 00:03:40,679
He even changed
his first diaper.

44
00:03:40,805 --> 00:03:45,810
- Did he?
- Yes.

45
00:03:45,935 --> 00:03:48,228
You need anything?
You want me to bring you
anything?

46
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:50,372
The bag with Valentina's stuff.

47
00:03:50,397 --> 00:03:51,565
Since it was going
to be a C-section,

48
00:03:51,690 --> 00:03:53,709
I left it at home.

49
00:03:53,734 --> 00:03:55,069
Just let me look at her
one more second

50
00:03:55,194 --> 00:03:58,172
and I'll go for it.

51
00:04:00,574 --> 00:04:02,093
You know?

52
00:04:02,118 --> 00:04:05,537
I'm glad I did it
naturally instead.

53
00:04:05,663 --> 00:04:07,665
It couldn't have gone
any better.

54
00:04:07,790 --> 00:04:10,768
I'm so proud of you.

55
00:05:28,537 --> 00:05:29,930
Hi, dad.

56
00:05:29,955 --> 00:05:31,682
Hi, daddy.

57
00:05:31,707 --> 00:05:36,461
I was in the shower
and didn't hear the phone.

58
00:05:36,587 --> 00:05:40,340
I overslept, but
I'm on my way, I swear.

59
00:05:40,382 --> 00:05:42,484
Yes, I'm on my way right now.

60
00:05:42,509 --> 00:05:45,445
Okay, see you. Bye.

61
00:05:45,470 --> 00:05:50,409
Baby, I have to go.

62
00:05:50,434 --> 00:05:52,452
Bye.

63
00:05:58,358 --> 00:05:59,710
Hey, I think somebody

64
00:05:59,735 --> 00:06:01,962
broke in.

65
00:06:01,987 --> 00:06:04,965
It's all right.

66
00:06:26,011 --> 00:06:27,405
No, please, no.

67
00:06:27,429 --> 00:06:29,407
Please, no!

68
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:35,662
Son of a bitch!

69
00:06:41,693 --> 00:06:44,629
This week was tough.

70
00:06:46,657 --> 00:06:50,052
Really tough.

71
00:06:50,077 --> 00:06:53,055
It was my birthday and...

72
00:06:53,080 --> 00:06:54,681
You know how everything

73
00:06:54,706 --> 00:06:57,642
turns into a temptation.

74
00:06:57,668 --> 00:07:00,645
I didn't feel good.

75
00:07:02,881 --> 00:07:06,485
So I called my boss

76
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:09,488
and I told him

77
00:07:09,513 --> 00:07:12,491
that I was sick.

78
00:07:14,601 --> 00:07:18,063
I think my boss
didn't like it.

79
00:07:18,189 --> 00:07:21,917
But what could I do?

80
00:07:21,942 --> 00:07:25,612
As soon as I got out on the
street and met a friend...

81
00:07:25,737 --> 00:07:28,173
Damn!

82
00:07:28,199 --> 00:07:32,303
I'd fall back.

83
00:07:32,328 --> 00:07:35,080
It's better to be alone
than in bad company.

84
00:07:39,793 --> 00:07:42,546
I've got one year clean
to the day.

85
00:07:44,673 --> 00:07:48,068
I'm clean.

86
00:07:48,093 --> 00:07:51,029
I haven't fallen.

87
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:57,495
Bye.

88
00:07:57,519 --> 00:07:59,497
So how are you?

89
00:07:59,521 --> 00:08:03,067
Fine, daddy.
Fine.

90
00:08:03,192 --> 00:08:06,278
Well, tell me something
about you.

91
00:08:06,404 --> 00:08:08,630
There's not much to tell.

92
00:08:08,655 --> 00:08:10,324
Everything is
just the same.

93
00:08:10,449 --> 00:08:13,577
I just work on
my drawings,

94
00:08:13,702 --> 00:08:15,887
a take care of my plants.

95
00:08:15,913 --> 00:08:17,122
My days are
pretty boring,

96
00:08:17,248 --> 00:08:19,641
but that's good news.

97
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:22,169
That means I'm doing
all right.

98
00:08:22,294 --> 00:08:26,273
Yes, but you look tired.

99
00:08:26,298 --> 00:08:28,508
- Are you getting enough sleep?
- Yes.

100
00:08:28,633 --> 00:08:30,694
Yes, the thing is...

101
00:08:30,719 --> 00:08:33,722
I'm working
an a new schedule.

102
00:08:33,847 --> 00:08:35,699
I get inspired at night

103
00:08:35,724 --> 00:08:37,326
and I'm working on a tattoo

104
00:08:37,351 --> 00:08:38,643
that has me
sort of obsessed.

105
00:08:38,769 --> 00:08:41,205
But it's almost finished.

106
00:08:41,230 --> 00:08:44,483
I don't like you working
in that place.

107
00:08:44,608 --> 00:08:46,860
I've already told you
it's not the same

108
00:08:46,985 --> 00:08:48,546
as working at a bar.

109
00:08:48,570 --> 00:08:51,156
Yes, but people
who get tattoos...

110
00:08:51,282 --> 00:08:52,632
I don't think they're--

111
00:08:52,657 --> 00:08:54,593
Look, I know, I know.

112
00:08:54,618 --> 00:08:56,887
But I'm telling you

113
00:08:56,912 --> 00:08:58,122
that not everyone
who gets a tattoo

114
00:08:58,247 --> 00:08:59,639
is on drugs.

115
00:08:59,664 --> 00:09:01,517
No, but most do.

116
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:03,168
I'm talking about
healthy students.

117
00:09:03,294 --> 00:09:04,753
Nice little guys that go
and get a tattoo.

118
00:09:04,795 --> 00:09:06,689
That's all.

119
00:09:06,713 --> 00:09:08,006
It's not the same
it used to be.

120
00:09:08,132 --> 00:09:09,591
- I hope so.
- Yes.

121
00:09:09,716 --> 00:09:11,427
But let's talk
about something else.

122
00:09:11,551 --> 00:09:12,844
- How's your job doing?
- Fine.

123
00:09:12,970 --> 00:09:15,514
Sometimes I have to work
double shift,

124
00:09:15,639 --> 00:09:17,599
they haven't raised my salary
in three years.

125
00:09:17,724 --> 00:09:19,326
We have a lot of work.

126
00:09:19,351 --> 00:09:21,979
Some are working abroad
and they get a better pay,

127
00:09:22,104 --> 00:09:24,289
they have holidays.

128
00:09:24,315 --> 00:09:27,292
Are you seeing anyone?

129
00:09:30,779 --> 00:09:34,866
Look like we're playing
not to talk about oneself

130
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:36,285
and get information
from the other.

131
00:09:36,410 --> 00:09:37,802
But I asked you first.

132
00:09:37,828 --> 00:09:39,163
No.
- Yes.

133
00:09:39,288 --> 00:09:40,664
No, I'm not seeing
anyone.

134
00:09:40,789 --> 00:09:42,500
And you?
Is there anyone?

135
00:09:42,624 --> 00:09:44,142
I'm just asking

136
00:09:44,168 --> 00:09:46,128
because the other day
when I went to your place,

137
00:09:46,253 --> 00:09:49,256
the guy next door
sort of wanted to talk to me.

138
00:09:49,298 --> 00:09:51,316
Or kind of, right?

139
00:09:51,342 --> 00:09:56,221
Must be because he knows
you're the owner.

140
00:09:56,263 --> 00:09:57,282
You don't believe me?

141
00:09:57,306 --> 00:09:59,057
Why would he want
to talk to you?

142
00:09:59,099 --> 00:10:01,076
Dad, I'm not seeing anyone.

143
00:10:01,101 --> 00:10:03,312
I don't want
to be with anyone now,

144
00:10:03,437 --> 00:10:04,913
much less your tenant.

145
00:10:04,938 --> 00:10:06,648
My life is way too
complicated

146
00:10:06,773 --> 00:10:08,708
to get in deeper trouble.

147
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:11,278
I don't know.
I just think

148
00:10:11,403 --> 00:10:13,197
sometimes it's good
to get someone

149
00:10:13,322 --> 00:10:15,073
to be with you,
you get me?

150
00:10:15,199 --> 00:10:17,342
At least to drink some wine.

151
00:10:17,368 --> 00:10:19,286
- Whatever.
- Yes.

152
00:10:19,411 --> 00:10:21,955
It's so weird to talk
about this with you, dad.

153
00:10:21,997 --> 00:10:23,515
For real.

154
00:10:23,541 --> 00:10:25,334
Just stop it.
Let's discuss something else.

155
00:10:25,459 --> 00:10:27,169
Let's get some breakfast.
I didn't eat anything.

156
00:10:27,294 --> 00:10:28,853
Fine, I'm sorry.

157
00:10:28,879 --> 00:10:30,506
You didn't have breakfast?
That's what I'm talking about.

158
00:10:30,630 --> 00:10:33,692
Are we starting all over?

159
00:10:33,717 --> 00:10:36,470
- I'm hungry, that's all.
- Okay, I'll pay. Let's go.

160
00:10:41,141 --> 00:10:43,894
She's just like her
mom.

161
00:10:55,406 --> 00:10:58,425
I'll get it.

162
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:19,863
Hello?

163
00:11:23,642 --> 00:11:26,620
Who was that?

164
00:11:26,645 --> 00:11:29,623
They hanged up.

165
00:11:35,237 --> 00:11:36,714
I won!

166
00:11:36,738 --> 00:11:39,157
Watch your reflexes.
Hello?

167
00:11:39,283 --> 00:11:40,925
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Hello, Walter. It's me.</font></i>

168
00:11:40,951 --> 00:11:45,581
Hi, Carmen, did you
hear the news?

169
00:11:45,705 --> 00:11:47,182
Can you talk now?

170
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:51,186
Yes, she's so beautiful.

171
00:11:51,211 --> 00:11:54,814
Yes, she did it great.

172
00:11:54,839 --> 00:11:56,508
Why are you calling me
home,

173
00:11:56,634 --> 00:11:58,068
fucking junkie?

174
00:11:58,093 --> 00:12:00,278
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Yes, I know, I know, bitch.</font></i>

175
00:12:00,304 --> 00:12:02,447
I called your cell phone

176
00:12:02,473 --> 00:12:03,823
and you didn't answer.

177
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:05,367
It's an emergency.

178
00:12:05,392 --> 00:12:07,311
Somebody broke in my place.
I got robbed.

179
00:12:07,436 --> 00:12:08,870
What?

180
00:12:08,895 --> 00:12:10,330
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Yes, all the product.</font></i>

181
00:12:10,355 --> 00:12:11,665
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">The blue meth is gone.</font></i>

182
00:12:11,690 --> 00:12:13,124
It's a mystery.

183
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,543
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Are you listening?</font></i>

184
00:12:14,568 --> 00:12:15,944
This is serious
stuff!

185
00:12:16,069 --> 00:12:17,362
They knew exactly
where to look for it.

186
00:12:17,488 --> 00:12:20,324
It's as though
they were watching us.

187
00:12:20,449 --> 00:12:22,576
Walter, say something!
Answer me!

188
00:12:22,701 --> 00:12:23,868
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Scream at me!</font>
<font face="monospaceSansSerif">So something!</font></i>

189
00:12:23,994 --> 00:12:25,470
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Just react!</font></i>

190
00:12:25,496 --> 00:12:29,974
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Hello? Walter? Walter?</font></i>

191
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:32,018
Damn!

192
00:12:48,477 --> 00:12:51,830
<i><font face="monospaceSansSerif">Family, chicken is here.</font></i>

193
00:12:51,855 --> 00:12:54,792
Joint, legs, tights.

194
00:12:54,816 --> 00:12:56,710
What do you want?

195
00:12:56,735 --> 00:12:59,655
- Cool.
- Watch it. It's hot.

196
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:03,617
- Smells good.
- Yes, it smells delicious.

197
00:13:03,742 --> 00:13:04,993
- Pollos Hermanos?
- Yes, yes.

198
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:07,412
The name is not that good,
but the moment you try

199
00:13:09,665 --> 00:13:11,141
those tights,

200
00:13:11,166 --> 00:13:13,585
you won't ever forget it.
Believe me.

201
00:13:13,711 --> 00:13:15,587
We cops
eat lots of chicken.

202
00:13:15,713 --> 00:13:18,173
- Right, babe?
- Yes.

203
00:13:18,298 --> 00:13:20,066
She must be hungry.

204
00:13:20,091 --> 00:13:22,927
- You think so?
- Yes.

205
00:13:24,429 --> 00:13:26,865
Cielo...

206
00:13:26,890 --> 00:13:28,241
Cielo, just hold on.

207
00:13:28,266 --> 00:13:30,060
- Are you breasting her?
- Of course!

208
00:13:30,185 --> 00:13:31,745
Babe, please.

209
00:13:31,770 --> 00:13:33,855
The baby has to eat.
That's normal.

210
00:13:33,980 --> 00:13:36,816
Yes, but it's
my sister-in-law's breast.

211
00:13:36,941 --> 00:13:38,193
We're at the table.
Come on.

212
00:13:38,318 --> 00:13:39,837
Then look aside, Henry.

213
00:13:39,861 --> 00:13:41,572
That's even worse.
If you tell me "look aside",

214
00:13:41,697 --> 00:13:43,173
I'll want to look.

215
00:13:43,198 --> 00:13:44,366
Henry, can I ask
you something?

216
00:13:44,491 --> 00:13:46,009
Sure.

217
00:13:46,034 --> 00:13:47,786
You told me about
a security system

218
00:13:47,911 --> 00:13:49,304
for the baby.

219
00:13:49,329 --> 00:13:50,722
Yes, an intercom.

220
00:13:50,748 --> 00:13:52,140
Yes, that's it.

221
00:13:52,165 --> 00:13:53,809
Well, I was thinking

222
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,544
about something more
modern.

223
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:59,047
There are some alarms
with movement sensors

224
00:13:59,089 --> 00:14:00,882
in case something falls
on the floor and--

225
00:14:01,007 --> 00:14:02,426
- That sounds expensive.
- Thanks, aunt.

226
00:14:02,551 --> 00:14:05,303
Yes, but that's the best
for Valentina.

227
00:14:05,429 --> 00:14:08,948
Babe, we'll get that for you.

228
00:14:08,973 --> 00:14:10,408
No, no, it's not necessary.

229
00:14:10,434 --> 00:14:11,993
Come on, man!

230
00:14:12,018 --> 00:14:14,229
No, No.
Besides, I'll go back to work

231
00:14:14,354 --> 00:14:15,789
in a couple of days, so--

232
00:14:15,814 --> 00:14:19,025
- Back to work?
- Of course.

233
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:21,986
Babe, you have
a scheduled surgery.

234
00:14:22,112 --> 00:14:24,631
We have to pay for that.

235
00:14:24,656 --> 00:14:26,408
We have to keep
that income.

236
00:14:26,533 --> 00:14:28,343
Look.

237
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:31,830
We have to think about what's
best for the baby.

238
00:14:31,955 --> 00:14:34,750
And the best is for her
to be with her mom.

239
00:14:34,874 --> 00:14:37,294
At least during
the first year.

240
00:14:37,419 --> 00:14:39,838
If we get organized, I can take
care of everything.

241
00:14:39,963 --> 00:14:41,757
You guys got a printing press
in the garage

242
00:14:41,881 --> 00:14:44,484
churning out 50s?

243
00:14:44,509 --> 00:14:47,929
I wish, uncle!
mom's even talking

244
00:14:47,971 --> 00:14:49,573
abut me getting a job.

245
00:14:49,598 --> 00:14:52,643
- Really?
- Of course..

246
00:14:52,768 --> 00:14:54,994
Some part-time job

247
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:56,705
that leaves him time to study.

248
00:14:56,730 --> 00:14:59,483
But he should help us
with the bills.

249
00:14:59,608 --> 00:15:02,444
Sure. I'll work
as a waiter.

250
00:15:02,569 --> 00:15:03,962
I don't get it.

251
00:15:03,987 --> 00:15:06,297
No one would hire me

252
00:15:06,323 --> 00:15:09,259
in a job like that.

253
00:15:16,916 --> 00:15:19,853
Give her the bottle.

254
00:15:19,878 --> 00:15:21,855
I'll get her.

255
00:15:21,880 --> 00:15:24,900
It's ready.

256
00:15:30,848 --> 00:15:34,075
Hi.

257
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,077
Come.

258
00:15:36,102 --> 00:15:38,121
Yes.

259
00:15:44,653 --> 00:15:47,447
You want to see what daddy
did for you?

260
00:15:57,207 --> 00:16:00,852
All this is yours.

261
00:16:00,878 --> 00:16:03,814
Daddy got it for you.

262
00:16:08,552 --> 00:16:10,554
This place
looks exactly the same.

263
00:16:10,679 --> 00:16:12,556
At least get some
computers.

264
00:16:12,681 --> 00:16:14,224
It's the 21st
century.

